full_text.87: It's not ten Hag's fault that Ronaldo barely scored goals when he started. He had numerous opportunities and he was regularly bested by an injury-prone Martial. Ten Hag just wants to make this team functional again and it just never clicked when Ronaldo was starting.
full_text.88: In hindsight, this explains why Ronaldo never really mentioned ten Hag in his cryptic "apology" after the Spurs game. He thinks that ten Hag disrespected him for wanting to sub him in with a few minutes left in the game.
full_text.89: Ronaldo claiming that ten Hag doesn't respect him doesn't make much sense. Ten Hag's comments on Ronaldo have largely been positive, although he clearly doesn't see Ronaldo in his long-term plans at all.
